{"serial": "93005", "department_serial": 29, "code": "EG1001", "class": "E", "name": {"en": "Programming for Engineering", "ch": "工程程式設計"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "搭配E2-129;工學院學士班請自行選課"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chih-Yang Lin"], "ch": ["林智揚"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["5", "6", "7"]}, "loc": {"building": "E2", "room": "308"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 70, "department": {"ch": "工學院", "en": "College of Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 55, "remark": {"ch": "搭配E2-129;工學院學士班請自行選課", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "計算機在我們的日常生活和工業中發揮著重要作用。 例如，工業中的大部分流程都是由計算機控制的； 理論計算和分子模擬是工程師和科學家進行研究和產品開發的重要工具。 本課程的主要目的是向未來的機械系學生介紹 C/C++ 作為編程工具。 該課程將採取務實的方法，將實際的工程和科學問題納入其應用和示例。", "en": "Computers play an important role in our daily life and in industry. For example, most of processes in industry are controlled by computers; theoretical computation and molecular simulation are important tools for engineers and scientists for doing research and product development. The main purpose of this course is to introduce C/C++ as a programming tool for future chemical and material engineers. The course will take a pragmatic approach that incorporates actual engineering and science problems for its applications and examples."}, "outline": {"ch": "「程式設計」通常被視為一位傑出理工人員所應具備的能力之一。在眾多的程式語言中，C/C++除具有直接處理位元運算的能力與高度的結構性之外，還引入物件導向的概念，因此舉凡從軟、硬體設計到韌體、系統開發，C/C++總是扮演不可或缺的角色之一。\n本課程將教授C/C++程式語言，讓同學瞭解整個程式設計的概念，學習如何用邏輯思考方式來拆解問題，再以有系統的方式組合成程式加以解決問題。此外，C/C++為各類開發與應用軟體的基礎，對後續學習相關的應用與軟體開發有相當的助益。學生將能展現以下的能力：\n1.熟悉C/C++的開發環境與介面，建構出應用程式\n2.瞭解程式的結構區塊\n3.具備程式設計的能力\n4.邏輯思考能力\n5.透過程式語言，作為各領域研究之輔助工具，例如：數值求解、解聯立方程、圖形表現等", "en": "“Programming“ is generally regarded as one of the abilities that an outstanding engineer should possess. Among many programming languages, in addition to the ability to directly process bit operations and a high degree of structure, C/C++also introduces the concept of object orientation. Therefore, from software and hardware design to firmware and system development, C/C++ is always Play one of the integral roles.\nThis course will teach the C/C++ programming language, allowing students to understand the concept of programming, learn how to use logical thinking to disassemble problems, and then combine them into programs in a systematic way to solve problems. In addition, C/C++ is the foundation of all kinds of development and application software, which is quite helpful to the development of application and software related to subsequent learning. Students will be able to demonstrate the ability to:\n1. Familiar with the development environment and interface of C/C++, and construct the application program\n2. Understand the structural blocks of the program\n3. Ability to program\n4. Logical thinking ability\n5. Through the programming language, as an auxiliary tool for research in various fields, such as: numerical solution, simultaneous equation solution, graphic representation, etc."}, "textbook": {"ch": "1. C程式設計藝術(第八版)(國際版)  作者： Deitel、全華翻譯小組  出版社：全華 \n\n2. C Programming Language, 2nd Edition 2nd Edition, Pearson; 2nd edition \n\n3. The C++ Programming Language, 4th Edition, Addison-Wesley Professional; 4th edition", "en": "1. C How to Program: With Case Studies in Applications and Systems Programming, Global Edition, by Paul Deitel, Harvey Deitel, Publisher ‏ : ‎ Pearson; 9th edition (May 23, 2022). ISBN-10: 1292437073, ISBN-13: 978-1292437071\n\n2. C Programming Language, 2nd Edition 2nd Edition, Pearson; 2nd edition \n\n3. The C++ Programming Language, 4th Edition, Addison-Wesley Professional; 4th edition"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "80", "en": "80"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "期中考：30％、期末考：30％、作業(含小考)：30％、課堂表現：10％", "en": "Mid-term exam: 30％, final exam: 30％, homework (including quiz): 30％, classroom performance: 10％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期一下午", "en": "Monday afternoon"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "最後兩周將安排自主學習、專題、實作等學習活動，最後將進行專題期末報告", "en": "During the 17th and 18th weeks, self-directed study, projects, hands-on practice, and other learning activities will be arranged. Finally, a final project presentation will take place."}, "domain": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "具備運用數學、科學、工程知識以及現代化工具解決工程領域問題之能力", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "具備發掘問題、設計規劃、實驗分析、詮釋數據與執行工程專題與專業之能力", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "具備專業表達、語言、撰寫之能力", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "具備溝通整合、團隊合作與領導之多元發展之能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考"]}, {"competencies": "具備產業結構之洞察力，社會責任之認知與永續經營之理念", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考"]}, {"competencies": "具備工程倫理與人文素養、強化國際觀，並養成終身學習之動力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限機械工程學系。年級:限一年級。班別:限B。", "系所:限機械工程學系。年級:限二年級、三年級、四年級。", "系所:限工學院學士班。年級:限一年級。", "系所:限工學院學士班。"], "en": ["Department:Department of Mechanical Engineering only.Year:First Year only.Class:B only.", "Department:Department of Mechanical Engineering only